<p>&nbsp;</p>
<hr style="clear: both;" />
<p><strong><span style="font-size: 18px;"><a href="http://www.brookings.edu/research/reports/2013/07/vital-statistics-congress-legislative-productivity-workload-mann-ornstein"><strong><span style="font-size: 18px;">Chapter 6: Legislative Productivity in Congress &amp; Workload</span></strong></a></span></strong></p>
<p><a href="http://www.brookings.edu/research/reports/2013/07/vital-statistics-congress-legislative-productivity-workload-mann-ornstein"><img style="width: 90px; float: left; height: 90px;  margin-right: 10px;border: 0px solid;" alt="Workload" src="http://www.brookings.edu/~/media/Multimedia/Interactives/2013/stats/icons/stats_icons07.jpg" /></a>How much has each Congress accomplished over the years, and how does the most recent Congress&rsquo; productivity compare to those of legislative bodies past? Chapter 6 reviews legislative productivity in the House and Senate over time, providing detailed data on number and length of bills passed, recorded votes in both chambers and the use of cloture motions in the Senate, among other data points.</p>
