<p>&nbsp;</p>
<hr style="clear: both;" />
<p><strong><span style="font-size: 18px;"><a href="http://www.brookings.edu/research/reports/2013/07/vital-statistics-congress-federal-budget-mann-ornstein"><strong><span style="font-size: 18px;">Chapter 7: Congressional Action on the Federal Budget</span></strong></a></span></strong></p>
<p><a href="http://www.brookings.edu/research/reports/2013/07/vital-statistics-congress-federal-budget-mann-ornstein"><img style="width: 90px; float: left; height: 90px;  margin-right: 10px;border: 0px solid;" alt="Federal Budget" src="http://www.brookings.edu/~/media/Multimedia/Interactives/2013/stats/icons/stats_icons08.jpg" /></a>Chapter 7&rsquo;s tables provide insight into Congress&rsquo; work on the federal budget, including votes in both chambers on adopting budget resolutions and other budget-related measures, spending and appropriations, and the use of continuing resolutions to keep the government funded.</p>
