<p><a href="http://www.brookings.edu/research/reports/2013/07/vital-statistics-congress-political-polarization-voting-alignments-mann-ornstein"><img style="width: 90px; float: left; height: 90px;  margin-right: 10px;border: 0px solid;" alt="Political Polarization" src="http://www.brookings.edu/~/media/Multimedia/Interactives/2013/stats/icons/stats_icons09.jpg" /></a>Chapter 8 documents the rise in political polarization in Congress and trends in voting alignment. The data includes ideological scores for House and Senate party coalitions and committees, party unity votes and scores, and roll call votes on bills on which the president has taken an official position.</p>
